==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Arcade
<hw>Ar*cade"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>arcade</ets>, Sp. <ets>arcada</ets>, LL. <ets>arcata</ets>, fr. L.
<ets>arcus</ets> bow, arch.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A series of arches with the columns or piers which
support them, the spandrels above, and other necessary appurtenances;
sometimes open, serving as an entrance or to give light; sometimes
closed at the back (as in the cut) and forming a decorative
feature.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A long, arched building or
gallery.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An arched or covered passageway or avenue.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Arcaded</ent>⟦br⟧
